Sentencas: PrBaCo2O5+delta (PBCO) powder was prepared by a combined EDTA and citrate complexing method.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of PrBaCo2O5+δ layered perovskite as an intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell cathode

Sentencas: The electrochemical performance of PBCO as a cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs) was evaluated.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of PrBaCo2O5+δ layered perovskite as an intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell cathode

Sentencas: A porous layer of PBCO was deposited on a 42 mu m thick electrolyte consisting of Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 (SDC), prepared by a dry-pressing process.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of PrBaCo2O5+δ layered perovskite as an intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell cathode

Sentencas: A fuel cell with a structure PBCO/SDC/Ni-SDC provides a maximum power density of 866,583, 313 and 115 mW cm(-2) at 650, 600,550 and 500 degrees C, respectively, using hydrogen as the fuel and stationary air as the oxidant.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of PrBaCo2O5+δ layered perovskite as an intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell cathode

Sentencas: The total resistance of the cell was about 0.41,0.51,0.57 and 0.77 Omega cm(2), respectively.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of PrBaCo2O5+δ layered perovskite as an intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell cathode

Sentencas: This encouraging data identifies PBCO as a potential cathode material for IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of PrBaCo2O5+δ layered perovskite as an intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell cathode
